subSubSection.paragraph:
Closest to 
Chamberlinius hualienensis
, but differs in being obviously smaller, with paraterga like low ridges (versus higher ridges in 
Chamberlinius hualienensis
), the pleurosternal carinae are 
with
small caudal teeth on segments 3-10 (versus 3-7(8) in 
Chamberlinius hualienensis
), legs with tarsal brushes (versus without in 
Chamberlinius hualienensis
) and the gonopods showing the tip of the solenophore pointed and simple (versus bifid in 
Chamberlinius hualienensis
).
